node.text:
This week, instead of sipping, we’re snacking. Contributing editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker) is back in Riviera Nayarit, Mexico at One&Only Mandarina (@oomandarina) cooking with Executive Chef Olivier Deboise (@olideboise). Chef’s Fire-Roasted Gratinated Oysters are sure to be a hit at your next summer party.
.
Ingredients:
½ dozen oysters
1 ½ oz butter
1 ½ oz aged goat cheddar
½ tsp shallots, diced
½ tsp Serrano chili, chopped
½ tsp epazote, julienned
Zest of 1 lemon
Zest of 1 lime 
.
Top each oyster with ¼ oz of butter and divide the chopped ingredients, lemon zest, and lime zest among the oysters. Top with grated aged goat cheddar. Grill over a medium to low flame for three to four minutes and brûlée for one and a half minutes. Serve hot.

node.title: These Fire-Roasted Oysters Are the Perfect Summer Appetizer

node.text: Next up on Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) visits One&Only Mandarina (@oomandarina) in beautiful Riviera Nayarit, Mexico, where Mixologist Ivan Aguilar shows us how to make one of his favorite cocktails. Of course, no trip to Mexico is complete without tequila, so naturally, that’s our spirit of choice for this episode. In fact, Ivan shows us that tequila can be used to add a twist to cocktails that traditionally use other liquors. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Calling All Tequila Lovers, This Cocktail Could Become Your New Favorite

node.text: On the latest episode of Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) heads to his hometown of Buffalo, New York to learn how to make three different summertime cocktails from head bartender at Lloyd Taco Factory (@lloydtacofactory), Jon Wheelock (@jwheels1). We won't give away what they're making, but we will say, if gin is your spirit of choice, you're in for a treat. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.text: Introducing Sipping With, a new series hosted by Contributing Editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker), who’s taking us behind the bar at world-renowned restaurants, hotels, and resorts to see how the best in the business craft specialty cocktails. Cheers!

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: the island of Amorgos, Greece. Luckily, there are more than 200 inhabited islands in Greece, meaning you can get all of the beauty and none the crowds on some of the lesser-known islands, like Amorgos. Come along! node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: Los Angeles’ famous East Hollywood neighborhood. You probably know Hollywood for its Walk of Fame, but there’s a lot more to the area than the glitz and glamour. The neighborhood is a melting pot of culture with a fascinating history. Come along! Tour by @lawalkingtours

node.title: Experience Hollywood Beyond the Glitz and Glamour on This Walking Tour

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: Austin, Texas. This tour of downtown Austin by @blackaustintours focuses on the experiences of the Black community, as well as its contributions to the city. We’ll learn about the history of places like the Texas State Capitol, Congress Avenue, and more. Come along.

node.title: Learn the History of the Black Community in Austin on This Walking Tour

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: The Holiday Tour of New York City. In a normal year, millions of visitors would be traveling to the Big Apple to see it decked out for the holiday season. This year, however, most of those visitors will be staying home, which is why we decided to bring New York City’s holiday cheer to you. Join us as we visit the Rockefeller Christmas Tree, Radio City Music Hall, and more. Happy holidays! Tour by @topdogtoursnyc

node.title: Stuck at Home This Christmas? Join Us on the Holiday Tour of New York City

This week on our podcast, guest host Tanner Saunders (@tizanner), T+L experiences editor, sits down with ‘Mean Girls’ star Jonathan Bennett (@jonathandbennett) and fiancé Jaymes Vaughan (@jaymesv) to chat about plans for their new LGBTQ+ cruise company, OUTbound Travel (@outbound_travel).
.
Click the link in bio to listen on Apple Podcasts, or listen wherever you get your podcasts.

node.text:
The next era of space exploration and innovation is here — and we're all invited. A billionaire space race is underway as Blue Origin, Virgin Galactic, SpaceX, and others are testing the technology to take us to places previously visited only by highly trained astronauts. Space tourism is officially taking flight, and it might just save the Earth.
.
We took a deep dive into the future of space tourism and what it means for us and our planet. We talked to astronauts, people who plan to be space tourists, and more. Read the coverage at the link in bio. 🚀🌚

node.text: Ready to take your love of hiking to the next level? Backpacking allows you to go deeper, stay longer, and in some cases, lose the crowds. Get our list of the best trips around the world at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Big Sur, California with @derekrliang. May be an image of twilight, tree, nature, coast and ocean.

node.text: When it comes to road trips, California is hard to top. You can start at the ocean and end up in the mountains, or spend an entire weekend exploring the deserts. To help you narrow down all of the options, get our list of the best Golden State road trips, from Big Sur to the Sierras, at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @derekrliang

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Château de Pierrefonds with @malteheitmueller. May be an image of castle and outdoors.

node.text: From fairy-tale castles to the sandy beaches of the Mediterranean, a trip to France deserves a spot on every traveler's bucket list. Get our guide at the link in bio. 🇫🇷 #tlpicks courtesy of @malteheitmueller

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How to Pack Lghter, Smarter, and Faster, According to T+L Editors'.

node.text: No matter the length of the trip — be it a weekend beach getaway or a three-week Himalayan trek — you'll need to pack a bag, and you’ll want to pack it right. Get a list of the 18 most important packing tips, according to T+L editors, at the link in bio.
